{"title_page": "Otto Lehmann-Russb\u00fcldt", "text_new": "{{Underlinked|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Otto Lehmann-Russb\u00fcldt''' (1 January 1873, Berlin \u2013 7 October 1964) was a [[German people|German]] pacifist activist and writer.<ref name=\"DB\">{{cite web|title=Lehmann-Ru\u00dfb\u00fcldt,|url=https://www.deutsche-biographie.de/downloadPDF?url=sfz49885.pdf.|website=Deutsche Biographie \u2013 Onlinefassung|publisher=Historische Kommission bei der Bayerischen Akademie der Wissenschaften|accessdate=26 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\nGerman:\n* (1919) ''Jung-Fr\u00fchling'' (autobiographical novel), Berlin\n* (1922) ''Die Br\u00fccke \u00fcber den Abgrund. F\u00fcr die Verst\u00e4ndigung zwischen Deutschland und Frankreich'', Berlin\n* (1926) Carl Mertens, Otto Lehmann-Ru\u00dfb\u00fcldt, [[Walter Kreiser|Konrad Widerhold]] : ''Die deutsche Milit\u00e4rpolitik seit 1918'', Berlin\n* (1926) ''Der Kampf der Deutschen Liga f\u00fcr Menschenrechte, vormals Bund Neues Vaterland, f\u00fcr den Weltfrieden 1914\u20131927'', Berlin\n* (1929) ''Die blutige Internationale der R\u00fcstungsindustrie'', Berlin\nEnglish:\n* (1936) ''Hitler's wings of death'' New York: Telegraph Press; ''Germany's air force'' London: G. Allen & Unwin\n* (1942) ''Aggression: The origin of Germany's war machine'', London: Hutchinson\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lehmann-Russbuldt, Otto}}\n[[Category:1873 births]]\n[[Category:1964 deaths]]\n[[Category:Writers from Berlin]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Brandenburg]]\n[[Category:German Peace Society members]]\n[[Category:German activists]]\n[[Category:German writers]]\n\n\n{{Germany-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Otto Lehmann-Russb\u00fcldt''' (1 January 1873, Berlin \u2013 7 October 1964) was a [[German people|German]] pacifist activist and writer.<ref name=\"DB\">{{cite web|title=Lehmann-Ru\u00dfb\u00fcldt,|url=https://www.deutsche-biographie.de/downloadPDF?url=sfz49885.pdf.|we